mixture through a fine mesh sieve. Discard sieve contents and reserve the liquid starter. This is a sour tasting starter that forms the base of the soup."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Soup"},{"content":"Place a small bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh 100 g of the water into it. Add porcini or shiitake mushrooms, then set aside to soak for 20 minutes."},{"content":"Place 400 g of the water into mixing bowl, insert simmering basket and place eggs into it. Cook <b>14 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and run eggs under cold water to cease cooking. Set boiled eggs aside to cool completely. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place onion and garlic into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Add oil and sauté <b>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add bacon or speck and chorizo or Polish sausage and sauté <b>3 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add remaing 600 g of water, potatoes, stock paste, bay leaves and allspice, then cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add salt, pepper, 300 g of the reserved sourdough starter and soaked dried mushrooms with soaking water and cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add marjoram, horseradish (optional) and sour cream and cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Peel hardboiled eggs and cut into quarters. Serve soup immediately, garnished with hardboiled egg."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Leftover starter will last in the refrigerator in a sealed jar for 2-3 days and can be used to make a 2nd batch of soup.","Serve soup with crusty bread on the side."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","96h 30m","4 portions"]}